# Frontend (web/) — React 18 + Vite + TS + shadcn/ui

Adapted from `awesome-cursorrules/cursor-ai-react-typescript-shadcn-ui`
and `react-query`, trimmed to match the locked stack in `00-project.mdc`.

> **Important:** this app is plain Vite + React. We do **not** use Next.js,
> the App Router, `use client`, server components, or SSR. Ignore any
> generic advice that mentions them.

## Style and structure

- Functional components only. No class components.
- TypeScript everywhere. Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes
  unless you need a union/mapped type.
- Avoid `enum`s; use `as const` maps or string literal unions.
- Lowercase-with-dashes for directories (`components/cluster-card`,
  `pages/logs-surgeon`). PascalCase for React component filenames is fine
  (`ClusterCard.tsx`).
- Co-locate component, its styles, and its tests. Keep one exported
  component per file unless they're tightly coupled subcomponents.
- Favor named exports over default exports.

## UI and styling

- Tailwind CSS, mobile-first. Compose with `clsx` / `cn` (the standard
  shadcn helper) instead of conditional class strings.
- Use shadcn/ui primitives (`Button`, `Card`, `Dialog`, `Table`, etc.)
  before reaching for ad-hoc markup. Generate new shadcn components into
  `web/src/components/ui/` via the shadcn CLI and check them in.
- Dark mode is the default; verify both modes look correct.
- Charts use **Recharts** (sparklines, retention Gantt, WAL timeline).
  Don't introduce additional chart libraries.

## Data fetching — TanStack Query

- One `QueryClient` + `QueryClientProvider` at the app root.
- Wrap every server interaction in a custom hook under
  `web/src/hooks/queries/` or `web/src/hooks/mutations/`. Pages and
  components must not call `useQuery` / `useMutation` inline.
- Use stable, structured query keys: `['clusters', clusterId, 'wal']`.
  Centralize key factories per domain in `web/src/api/keys.ts` (or similar)
  to keep invalidation correct.
- Implement loading and error states for every query. The "Logs Surgeon"
  view auto-refreshes every 5 minutes; an "Instant Snap" button forces a
  refetch.
- Use `staleTime` deliberately. Use `invalidateQueries` after mutations.
- Optimistic updates only for low-risk UX (e.g. ack alert). Never for
  pgBackRest job submission.
- Enable React Query DevTools in dev builds.

## Routing and pages

- Pages live in `web/src/pages/`: `Dashboard.tsx`, `Cluster.tsx`,
  `Logs.tsx`, `Jobs.tsx`, `Alerts.tsx`, `Login.tsx`.
- Use a small router (React Router v6) — no Next.js router.

## Auth

- UI talks to manager via `/api/v1/...`. Bearer JWT (HS256) in
  `Authorization`. Store the token in memory + `localStorage`; clear on
  401.
- Don't roll your own crypto. Don't decode the JWT on the client beyond
  reading `exp` for soft logout.

## Performance

- Code-split routes with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`.
- Memoize expensive Recharts datasets with `useMemo`. Avoid re-rendering
  the whole logs stream on every poll — virtualize long lists.
- Optimize images (WebP, explicit dimensions, lazy loading).

## Things to avoid

- No DaisyUI, no Material UI, no Chakra. shadcn/ui + Tailwind only.
- No Redux, MobX, Zustand, or Recoil. Local state + TanStack Query covers
  v1. Add a state lib only with explicit justification.
- No `any`. Use `unknown` + a type guard if the shape is genuinely dynamic.
- No inline `fetch` in components. Go through the typed `api/` client.
